				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Need advice, please.<a name="36425"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 25 04 11:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Here's what I have found to be successful for me in those style groups. 
<br />
#1 work the mob / mobs each down to 90% approximately before anyone in the group casts anything.. including snare or debuffs on any of the mobs. 
<br />
#2Then have them assist you so as they are blasting / dot'ing the same mob you are consistantly dotting to keep the agro firmly on you. 
<br />
#3 NO AE&gt;&gt;&gt; tell your wizards please don't AE because when they accede the agro you established with your initial 10% damage to the mob that npc in question will charge out of your kite and for the caster which is mis targeted. 
<br />
#4 Make sure when you pulse your 2 min selo's for yourself to include the casters so if they do take agro they have the option of kiting the mob themselves.. staying well ahead of the mob same as a bard stopping to cast or just keep its attention until the bard can reestablish agro without risking his own death by the other mobs still remaining in the kite. 
<br />
#5 If there are healers in your group be sure they understand not to heal you, until you call clear for heal. A mis timed heal could gain agro and bards have no taunt to save them. If your beaten on but then pull ahead you can heal yourself up with your song safer than they could time a heal on you as you pass without endangering themselves. 
<br />
#6 They white empty suits of armor are unsnareable and summon so be prepared to tank these if necessary if they happen to pop.. they are a very rare pop though. Also there are 2 types of human guards .. one is snare able one is not. They one that is not needs to be kited by someone with selo's its inherant speed is faster than rs3. 
<br />
I think its valorian guardians are snareable and do not summon
<br />
and Valorian Sentry's can not be snared but do not summon
<br />
I believe the one that summons and is unsnareable is called a valorious spirit and has white armor. I'm not posative ont he name though. </span></td>
